<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06101209 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06101209 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  CHART; RETAIL; SALE; STORE; GAMBLING; BUSINESS; COMPANY; STOCK; RANKING; LIST  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Retailer Wal-Mart stores was rated most responsive to its shareholders whileamusement conglomerate Bally Manufacturing was rated the least in a reportcard issued Tuesday on corporate management of 1,000 U.S. companies.;    Itwas the second year in a row that Wal-Mart topped the ratings issued by theUnited Shareholders Association.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  WAL-MART PLACES NO. 1 AGAIN  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Chart attached at end of article  </MEMO><TEXT>     The association is a Washington-based grass-roots advocacy organizationthat seeks to enhance the rights of shareholders and make corporate executivesmore accountable. It was founded by takeover strategist T. Boone Pickens in1986.;    The Shareholder 1,000 list measures corporate management by threeyardsticks: the company's bottom-line performance, which counts for 50 percentof every company's score; executive compensation, 25 percent; and recognitionof shareholder rights, also 25 percent.;    Arkansas-based Wal-Mart got thehighest overall rating, 84 out of a possible 100, by giving shareholders anaverage annual return of 44.4 percent over the last 10 years.;    In contrast,Bally's overall score was only 17.8 out of 100, with low marks for economicperformance.;    The Shareholder 1,000 ratings, in its third year, &quot;highlightsmanagement's accountability to shareholder interests,&quot; said associationPresident Ralph Whitworth.;    He admitted the list &quot;is a response to theother popular corporate ratings such as the Fortune 500&quot; ratings of thelargest U.S. corporations.;    &quot;But size is meaningless to shareholders,&quot;Whitworth told a news conference at the National Press Club.;    &quot;None of theother rankings say anything about how management performs for the owners ofthe corporation -- the shareholders,&quot; Whitworth added.; SHAREHOLDERS'RANKINGS; Wal-Mart topped the Shareholder 1,000 for the second straight year.Bally Manufacturing brought up the rear in the United ShareholdersAssociation's annual rating of companies' responsiveness to stockholders.; Top10                           Bottom 10; ...;  1. Wal-Mart                    1. Bally Manufacturing;  2. Blockbuster Ent.             2. Thiokol;  3.Golden West Fin.             3. Western Union;  4. Novell                      4. Unisys;  5. Autodesk                     5. Cetus;  6. Nike                        6. Data General;  7. FlightSafety Int'l           7. Bank of NewEngland;  8. Home Depot                   8. Tucson Electric Power;  9.Berkshire Hathaway           9. Quantum Chemical; 10. Biomet                     10. Gencorp; Source:   Associated Press; Mercury News  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Washington  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910410  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  2C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  CHART  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  354  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday April 10, 199100101209,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>